CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1973, pg. 10 reads:"Alpha Omegas Check Scores - Pictured above are members of the Ways and Means Committee of Alpha Alpha Omega Chapter of the Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, which hosted the fun-filled benefit luncheon card party recently in Cantina Room of the U.S. Steel Bldg., downtown. Checking scores for the awarding of the handsome prizes are, seated left to right, Cora Hatley, Patricia Huffman, Nan Lewis and Nona Douglas.  Standing, left to right, Barbara Douglas, Emylene Hayes and Alma Burgess. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women seated at square tables, playing cards during Alpha Kappa Alpha luncheon card party in the Cantina Room, U.S. Steel Building
